EARLY WARNING SIGNALS:
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
Pre-Announcement Patterns:
- Usually 2-3 weeks before earnings
- After market on Thursdays common
- Negative more likely than positive

Trading Pre-Announcements:
NEGATIVE PRE â†’ Stock drops 10-20%
Action: Buy after 2 days if quality
Success rate: 65% bounce

POSITIVE PRE â†’ Stock jumps 5-10%
Action: Buy more, earnings de-risked
Success rate: 72% continuation

NO PRE when expected â†’ Bearish
Action: Reduce or avoid
Success rate: 68% disappoints
SECTION 4: EXECUTION STRATEGIES
The Three-Phase Entry System
BUILDING POSITIONS STRATEGICALLY:
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
PHASE 1: STARTER (Day -10 to -7)
Size: 30% of intended position
Criteria:
- Historical beater confirmed
- No red flags in checks
- Technical setup positive
- Sector momentum good

PHASE 2: BUILD (Day -7 to -3)
Size: 40% of intended position
Criteria:
- Peers reporting well
- No negative pre-announce
- Maintaining momentum
- Options flow bullish

PHASE 3: FINAL (Day -3 to -1)
Size: 30% of intended position
Criteria:
- Final checks positive
- Price action strong
- Volume increasing
- Ready for gap up

ABORT SIGNALS (Exit all):
- Negative pre-announcement
- Peer disasters
- Technical breakdown
- Insider selling
