SCENARIO 1: BEAT & RAISE (Stock +5-10%)
Hour 1: Let it run, no action
Day 1: Set stop at open price
Day 2: Trail stop 5% from high
Week 1: Take 30% off at +15%
Week 2: Trail remainder at 7%

SCENARIO 2: BEAT & MAINTAIN (Stock +2-5%)
Hour 1: Watch for fade
Day 1: Add if holding gains
Day 2: Full position if strong
Week 1: Standard management
Week 2: Exit if momentum dies

SCENARIO 3: MISS BUT GUIDE OK (Stock -5-10%)
Hour 1: Do not panic sell
Day 1: Assess the damage
Day 2: Exit if not recovering
Week 1: Dead money, exit all

SCENARIO 4: DISASTER (Stock -15%+)
Hour 1: Exit immediately
Day 1: No averaging down
Day 2: Look elsewhere
Week 1: Document lessons
Options Overlay Strategies
ENHANCING EARNINGS TRADES:
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
Conservative: Covered Calls
- Own stock, sell calls above
- Target: 10% above current
- Expiry: Week after earnings
- Benefit: Extra income if flat

Aggressive: Call Spreads
- Buy ATM call
- Sell call 10% higher
- Expiry: Week after earnings
- Benefit: Leveraged but capped

Protective: Collar
- Own stock
- Buy put 5% below
- Sell call 10% above
- Benefit: Protected range

Speculative: Straddle Sales
- Sell ATM put and call
- Only on range-bound names
- High IV before earnings
- Benefit: Premium collection
